metadata.name: Word-eating worms #79
metadata.description:
Audiovisual generative artwork.

An old letter recounts the problems and feelings caused by woodworms: worms known to eat not only the beams and wood of houses, but also old books. As an analogy to this daily occurrence, emoticons appear and with the good spirit of simplifying they begin to gnaw away so much literary flourish.

The piece puts in counterpoint two forms of communication: emoticons and traditional writing. Here an inevitable contrast is sought between the standardization of the feelings of emojis, and the excessive flourishes of texts, possibly already from other times.

Original flute (tap & frullato), cello (pizz) and marimba samplers.

metadata.name: ylb-mess-A #189
metadata.description:
With colors and shapes reminiscent of childhood LEGO explorations, 'ylb-mess-A' explores the assembly process in reverse, using recursive subdivision to create detailed structures instead of progressively building a complex structure brick by brick. Although the tools I use to explore and create have changed over the years, this piece reminds me of the natural creative curiosity that was instilled in me at an early age, for which I am incredibly grateful.

metadata.name: Origin Undecided #1
metadata.description:
These feel like communications from an unknown place.

Ultimately, this is a deeper exploration of familiar concepts. The code generates patterns for a couple million lines, each with extremely low opacity. As they're drawn and overlap, the color accumulates and shapes begin to form.

Created by Eric Davidson. 2022.
